<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>CF 500, CF 600 Transmission - Transaxle / Transmission Cooling - Removal and Installation</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="11">
        <title>Removal and Installation</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Transmission Fluid Cooler Hoses</title>
            <figure id="f0702005" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0024814.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="352px"/>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">1. Transmission fluid cooler hose fittings</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">2. Rear transmission fluid remote filter fittings</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">3. Front transmission fluid remote filter fittings</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">4. Transmission fluid cooler hose radiator fittings</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">5. Plastic cable ties</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">6. Retaining clamps</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">7. Plastic retainer</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Transmission fluid cooler hoses between the remote filter and transmission</emph>
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the vehicle in NEUTRAL, position it on a hoist. For additional information, refer
                    to
                    <exhotlnk document="../S10/S10019.htm" bookname="S10019">Jacking and Lifting in S10019</exhotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">While holding the case fitting, disconnect both fluid cooler tubes at the
                    transmission.
                </para>
                <para>&#8226; To install, tighten to 40 Nm (30 lb-ft).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0702006" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0024805.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the nut from the cooler hose bracket at the extension housing.</para>
                <para>&#8226; To install, tighten to 10 Nm (89 lb-in).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0702007" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0024813.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the 2 transmission fluid cooler hoses from the rear of the remote filter.
                </para>
                <para>&#8226; To install, tighten to 40 Nm (30 lb-ft).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0702008" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0024612.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the transmission fluid cooler hoses from the vehicle. Transfer the retaining
                    clamps and the plastic cable ties to the new hoses.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Transmission fluid cooler hoses between the remote filter and radiator</emph>
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the 2 transmission fluid cooler hoses from the front of the remote filter.
                </para>
                <para>&#8226; To install, tighten to 40 Nm (30 lb-ft).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0702009" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0024815.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the nut from the cooler hose bracket on the LH side of the transmission.</para>
                <para>&#8226; To install, tighten to 10 Nm (89 lb-in).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0702010" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0024816.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the 3 tie straps and position the block heater and wiring harness aside.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0702011" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0024817.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the nut from the cooler hose bracket at the bellhousing.</para>
                <para>&#8226; To install, tighten to 10 Nm (89 lb-in).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0702012" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0024818.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the 3 cooler hose bracket nuts from the LH side of the engine.</para>
                <para>&#8226; To install, tighten to 10 Nm (89 lb-in).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0702013" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0024819.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the cooler hose retainer from the fan shroud.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0702014" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0024820.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the cooler hoses from the radiator.</para>
                <para>&#8226; To install, tighten to 40 Nm (30 lb-ft).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0702015" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0024821.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the transmission fluid cooler hoses from the vehicle and remove all of the band
                    clamps. Transfer the retaining clamps and the plastic cable ties to the new hoses.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">All vehicles</emph>
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Use only MERCON&#174; SP Transmission Fluid to service transmissions. Mixing MERCON&#174; or
                        MERCON&#174; V in a transmission may cause transmission damage. The use of any fluid other than
                        the recommended fluid can cause transmission damage.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Fill the transmission with clean automatic transmission fluid.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check for leaks.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To install, reverse the removal procedure.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
